1 2. "Delivered" shall mean transferred to the customer, either
2 immediately upon sale or at a time thereafter;
3 3. "Homemade food product" shall mean food, including a
4 beverage, which is produced and, if packaged, packaged at a
5 residence; provided, however, homemade food product shall not mean
6 alcoholic beverages or unpasteurized milk or cannabis or marijuana
7 products;
8 4. "Non-time- or -temperature-controlled for safety" shall mean
9 food that does not require time or temperature control for safety to
10 limit the rapid and progressive growth of infectious or toxigenic
11 microorganisms, including foods that have a pH level of four and
12 six-tenths (4.6) or below or a water activity (aw) value of eighty-
13 five one-hundredths (0.85) or less;
14 5. "Time- or temperature-controlled for safety" shall mean a
15 food that requires time or temperature control for safety to limit
16 infectious or toxigenic microorganisms and is in a form capable of
17 supporting rapid and progressive growth of infectious or toxigenic
18 microorganisms; provided, however, time- or temperature-controlled
19 for safety shall not include foods that have a pH level of four and
20 six-tenths (4.6) or below or a water activity (aw) value of eighty-
21 five one-hundredths (0.85) or less;
22 6. "Produce" shall mean to prepare a food product by cooking,
23 baking, drying, mixing, cutting, canning, fermenting, preserving,
24 dehydrating, growing, raising or other process; and
