3 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 5-4.3, as
4 amended by Section 1, Chapter 16, O.S.L. 2024 (2 O.S. Supp. 2024,
5 Section 5-4.3), is amended to read as follows:
6 Section 5-4.3. A. The production and sale of homemade food
7 products that meet the following conditions shall be exempt from all
8 licensing and other requirements of the State Department of Health
9 and the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry:
10 1. Non-time- or -temperature-controlled-for-safety homemade
11 food products shall be sold:
12 a. by the producer directly to the consumer, either in
13 person or by remote means, including, but not limited
14 to, the Internet or telephone, or
15 b. by a producer's designated agent or a third-party
16 vendor, such as a retail or grocery store, farm, farm
17 stand, farmers market, membership-based buying club,
18 craft fair or flea market, to the consumer; provided,
19 the third-party vendor displays a placard where
20 homemade food products are displayed for sale with the
21 following disclosure: "This product was produced in a
22 private residence that is exempt from government
23 licensing and inspection. This product may contain
24 allergens.";
Req. No. 10511 Page 3

1 2. Non-time- or -temperature-controlled-for-safety homemade
2 food products shall be delivered:
3 a. by the producer or producer's designated agent
4 directly to the consumer or third-party vendor, or
5 b. by a third-party vendor or a third-party carrier, such
6 as a parcel delivery service, to the consumer or a
7 third-party vendor;
8 3. Time- or temperature-controlled-for-safety homemade food
9 products shall be sold by the producer directly to the consumer,
10 either in person or by remote means, including, but not limited to,
11 the Internet or telephone;
12 4. Time- or temperature-controlled-for-safety homemade food
13 products shall be delivered by the producer directly to the
14 consumer;
15 5. Before a producer produces and sells time- or temperature-
16 controlled-for-safety homemade food products, the producer shall
17 complete and pass food safety training from a list of providers,
18 including the ServSafe Food Handler Training, approved by the
19 Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry. The food
20 safety training shall be available to complete online and shall not
21 exceed eight (8) hours in length. The Oklahoma Department of
22 Agriculture, Food, and Forestry shall make the list of approved
23 training available on its website by November 1, 2021;
24
Req. No. 10511 Page 4

1 6. The following information shall be provided to the consumer
2 in the format required by subsection B of this section:
3 a. the name and phone number of the producer,
4 b. the physical address where the product was produced,
5 c. a description of the homemade food product,
6 d. the ingredients of the homemade food product in
7 descending order of proportion,
8 e. a statement indicating the presence of any of the
9 eight most common allergens, including milk, eggs,
10 peanuts, tree nuts, soy and wheat, and
11 f. legible print stating, "This product was produced in a
12 private residence that is exempt from government
13 licensing and inspection.";
14 7. If the homemade food product is packaged and distributed in
15 interstate commerce, it shall also be sold and labeled in accordance
16 with federal law; and
17 8. Homemade food products shall not contain seafood or meat,
18 meat by-products or meat food products as defined by Section 301.2
19 of Title 9 of the Code of Federal Regulations or poultry, poultry
20 products or poultry food products as defined for purposes of the
21 federal Poultry Products Inspection Act; and
22 9. If the homemade food product consists of or contains
23 unpasteurized milk as an ingredient, the label shall contain the
24
