1 stat ement "Contains Unpasteurized Milk" and the placard shall
2 contain the statement "Contains Unpasteurized Milk".
3 B. The information required by paragraph 6 of subsection A of
4 this section shall be provided in a legible format of at least 10-
5 point font, in the following manner:
6 1. On a label affixed to the package if the homemade food
7 product is packaged;
8 2. On a label affixed to a container, if the homemade food
9 product is offered for sale from a bulk container directly to the
10 consumer;
11 3. On a placard displayed at the point of sale, and on a card
12 or other item that is made available to the consumer and is readily
13 carriable if the homemade food product is not packaged; and
14 4. Displayed on the webpage from which the homemade food
15 product is offered for sale if it is sold on the Internet; provided,
16 that each item sold over the Internet shall be properly labeled or
17 shall have a label included in the shipping container.
18 C. A homemade food product producer may obtain a registration
19 number upon the payment of an annual fee of Fifteen Dollars ($15.00)
20 to the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry that
21 is good for one (1) year from the date of its issue. The assigned
22 registration number may be used on product labels instead of the
23 producer's name, phone number, and the physical address of the
24 location where the homemade food product was produced.
